One (1) Information Management Assistant (H/F). ORGANIZATION DESCRIPTION :
Tanager is an international non-profit that connects smallholder producers and private businesses to co-create new ways of realizing life-changing economic and social opportunity.
Our process builds on years of technical expertise, on-the-ground presence and public/private partnerships to unite economic growth with social innovation. Together, we are ushering in an era of equitable market systems that combine profitability with the power to address urgent challenges in poverty, malnutrition and gender inequity.
MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES AND MISSIONS:
Under the supervision of the project director, the Information Management Assistant supports the collection, compilation, analysis, organization and distribution of information to project stakeholders.
As such, he/she will be responsible for:
Information and Data Management
Play a lead role in the design, development, management and improvement of data management systems, including databases and spreadsheets, and related data collection, cleaning and verification processes;
Drive thinking and innovation in monitoring and evaluation systems and tools;
Contribute to and facilitate program reflections among staff and partners to generate information relevant to program reporting and self-assessments on program-induced change processes
Collect, compile, analyze and report on a variety of primary and secondary data from a variety of sources and organize structural record keeping and archives.
Based on the data collected, conduct needs and gaps identification for the sector concerned;
Integrate, archive and retrieve large data sets for cross-referencing and statistical analysis, designing workflows and data collection templates as necessary;
Support and participate in analytical work by processing data and information into an appropriate format;
Write data queries for analysis using appropriate computer language;
Conduct ongoing monitoring of progress and performance;
Implement and regularly update the dissemination plan for all information management related products.
Studies and Evaluations
Participate in the design of periodic studies of the project;
Participate in the conduct of the project’s planned studies and research;
Support the learning objectives of the project, including the exploration of learning issues.
Reports/Documents
Participate in the preparation of data and information required for quarterly progress reports and project monitoring reports;
Participate in the review and finalization of study reports;
Systematically produce monitoring and evaluation mission reports with feedback to the partners visited;
Contribute to advancing the organization’s approach by sharing lessons learned, best practices and innovations with colleagues
Perform any other duties as requested by his/her superiors.
QUALIFICATIONS :
Have a minimum of a Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Monitoring and Evaluation, Management Information Systems, Demography, or equivalent;
Have extensive experience and knowledge of current data collection and monitoring and evaluation principles and approaches in nutrition-sensitive agriculture or market facilitation programs, using both quantitative and qualitative methods;
Have a minimum of three (3) years’ experience in database design and management, data processing and analysis;
Experience using innovative MEL methods such as outcome harvesting, most significant change, after action reviews and other qualitative and quantitative participatory methodologies is a strong asset;
Proficiency in the following software: Access, Sphinx, SPSS, CsPro, Epi-info;
Have a very good knowledge of digital data collection and practical experience in the use of software (ODK, Kobo, ONA, iForm, etc);
Proven experience in managing large and complex databases, web-based database experience is an asset;
Willingness to work under pressure;
Have strong written communication skills, including demonstrated ability to write required documents in a concise, clear and well-organized style;
Have strong demonstrated skills in the use of the Microsoft Office Suite, including Word, Excel and Powerpoint;
